**Data store:** `supabase.insightprofit.live` (self-hosted, same instance as `cos_brands`/`app_catalog`) — no separate database, no Convex dependency going forward

---

## 1. Executive Summary

Authority Engine started as a static SEO×AEO×GEO training course (landing page, 7 modules, a **manual** 50-point content scorecard where a human types in scores by hand, a 90-day roadmap). Separately, `SOP-ONDREJ-001` Phase 2 spec'd a live AI-answer-engine share-of-voice tracker as its own app (`aeo.insightprofit.live`) with a Convex backend. That second app was **partially built and run twice** (2026-05-20, 2026-06-01) against Perplexity only for 5 brands, synced its output into this Supabase instance, then was abandoned — no frontend was ever wired to it, and `aeo.insightprofit.live` never got a working deployment (TLS handshake fails outright; confirmed 2026-07-20).

This revision:
1. **Merges the live tracker into Authority Engine** (`/tracker` route) instead of resurrecting a second app at a domain nobody ever finished claiming.
2. **Recovers the abandoned 2026-05/06 audit data** rather than overwriting it — the existing `aeo_*` tables and their real history are preserved and extended, not re-seeded.
3. **Links `aeo_brands` to the real enterprise brand registry** (`cos_brands`, the `brand-registry-mapper` SSOT) via a new `cos_brand_id` foreign key, so AEO tracking isn't a disconnected 5-brand list.
4. **Adds the agentic output layer that never existed**: after every audit, an LLM synthesizes a structured content brief (gaps vs. competitors, recommended topics, recommended schema) per brand, stored in a new `aeo_content_briefs` table. The manual Scorecard is no longer the only signal — audits now *produce* something, not just measure.
5. **Routes all 4 engine personas (Perplexity/ChatGPT/Gemini/Claude) through OpenRouter**, one API key, any slot swappable to a cheaper or stronger model (including newer Kimi releases) without new credentials.

---

## 2. Provenance — what was found, what was recovered, what's new

This section exists because the prior state was easy to misread as "nothing was ever built." It wasn't — it was built, tested, and dropped mid-flight.

| Artifact | State found (2026-07-20) | Disposition |
|---|---|---|
| `aeo_brands`, `aeo_prompts`, `aeo_audits`, `aeo_audit_queries`, `aeo_competitors`, `aeo_sov_snapshots`, `aeo_cost_log` tables | **Already existed** in `supabase.insightprofit.live`, with `convex_id` columns showing they were originally written by a Convex app, synced here as a UMDM mirror. | Preserved. Not recreated, not re-seeded. |
| `aeo_v_brand_health`, `aeo_v_sov_trends` views | Already existed, ready-made for dashboard reads. | Now used directly by the Tracker frontend. |
| Real audit data | 10 completed audits (2 per brand × 5 brands), 70 audit_queries, 25 competitors (5/brand), across 2026-05-20 and 2026-06-01. **Perplexity only** — ChatGPT/Gemini/Claude were never run once. `aeo_cost_log` and `aeo_prompts` were empty despite existing (cost logging and a reusable prompt bank were never wired up). | Prompt bank backfilled from the 7 distinct historical `prompt_text` values per brand (migration 0001). Cost logging now writes on every run. |
| `aeo.insightprofit.live` domain | DNS CNAME → Vercel exists, but no Vercel project ever claimed it — TLS handshake fails, not even a 404. | Left as-is (not deleted per standing instruction). The tracker lives at `authority.insightprofit.live/tracker` instead; this domain can be aliased later or retired, both are your call. |
| `aeo-platform` repo | Tech spec + cursor rules only — zero implementation code. | Superseded by this doc; repo left untouched. |
| Agentic content-brief generation (`generateBrief` in the original tech spec) | Never built. `ai_content_briefs` table exists but is a generic per-document table unrelated to brand/audit data — not reusable for this. | Built new: `aeo_content_briefs` table + `generateBrief()` in `api/_lib/aeoAudit.ts`. |
| Command Center embed | Already wired (`v2-iframe-fleet.ts`, Content category) — but labeled "AI Creator Engine", the app's pre-rename name. | Label corrected, PR #26 merged. |
| Brand registry link | `aeo_brands` had no relationship to `cos_brands` — five brands existed only inside the AEO subsystem. | `cos_brand_id` FK added (migration 0001), backfilled for all 5 (InsightProfit, Funded First, Family Gift Studio, Faith Promises → `faithpromises` in cos_brands, Second Spring). |

**Why this matters operationally:** if you ever see the Tracker showing "0 audits" for a brand that you remember running, check `aeo_audits` directly before assuming data loss — the 2026-05/06 rows are real and load automatically once the frontend queries them correctly.

