## 3. Architecture (Tech Spec)

### 3.1 Data model (`supabase.insightprofit.live`, all tables RLS: anon read-only, service-role writes only)

```
aeo_brands (uuid id, name, slug, domain, color, vertical, is_active,
            last_sov_pct, last_audit_at, cos_brand_id → cos_brands.id)
  ├─ aeo_prompts (brand_id, text, intent, is_active)
  ├─ aeo_competitors (brand_id, name, domain)
  ├─ aeo_audits (brand_id, status, sov_pct, total_queries, total_mentions,
  │              engine_breakdown jsonb {engine: {total, mentions}}, cost_usd,
  │              started_at, completed_at)
  │    ├─ aeo_audit_queries (audit_id, brand_id, engine, prompt_text, prompt_intent,
  │    │                     raw_response, client_mentioned, client_position,
  │    │                     competitors_mentioned jsonb [{name, position}],
  │    │                     response_time_ms)
  │    └─ aeo_content_briefs (audit_id, brand_id, title, summary, gaps[],
  │                           recommended_topics[], recommended_schema[], model)  ← NEW
  ├─ aeo_sov_snapshots (brand_id, engine, sov_pct, total_queries, mentions, snapshot_date)
  └─ aeo_cost_log (audit_id, brand_slug, queries_count, estimated_cost_usd, provider, model)

aeo_v_brand_health   (view: per-brand rollup — total_audits, total_prompts, total_competitors, total_cost_usd)
aeo_v_sov_trends     (view: time series for charts)
```

One `aeo_audits` row = one full run for one brand across however many engines were requested (not one row per engine — `engine_breakdown` holds the per-engine split). This matches the schema that already existed; it is **not** the one-row-per-engine design an earlier draft of this work briefly used before the real schema was discovered.

### 3.2 Agentic workflow (the part that was missing)

```
Run Audit Now (or weekly cron)
  → for each engine × each active prompt:
      OpenRouter chat completion → extract brand/competitor mentions →
      write aeo_audit_queries row
  → aggregate → write aeo_audits (status=complete, sov_pct, engine_breakdown)
  → write aeo_cost_log + aeo_sov_snapshots
  → update aeo_brands.last_sov_pct / last_audit_at
  → generateBrief(): LLM call over the raw audit results →
      structured JSON {summary, gaps, recommended_topics, recommended_schema} →
      write aeo_content_briefs
```

Every run produces an artifact a human can act on (a brief), not just a percentage. This is the "not an empty checklist" requirement — the Scorecard's manual 0–5-per-criterion rating still exists for pages a human wants to eyeball, but it's no longer the only output of the AEO system.

### 3.3 Model routing (OpenRouter)

| Engine slot | Default model | Swappable to |
|---|---|---|
| Perplexity | `perplexity/sonar-pro` | any OpenRouter model |
| ChatGPT | `openai/gpt-4o` | incl. `openai/gpt-4o-mini` (cheap) |
| Gemini | `google/gemini-2.0-flash-001` | — |
| Claude | `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4` | incl. `anthropic/claude-3.5-haiku` (cheap) |
| Brief generation | `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4` (fixed) | — |

One API key (`OPENROUTER_API_KEY`) instead of four vendor keys. `moonshotai/kimi-k2` is listed as a preset (cheap, strong reasoning); the picker also accepts free text for any current model id, since exact slugs (e.g. a "Kimi 3" release) shift over time and shouldn't be hardcoded.

### 3.4 Endpoints (`authority-engine` repo)

- `api/aeo-audit.ts` — manual trigger, Node runtime (`maxDuration: 120`), `POST {brandId, engines?, models?}`.
- `api/cron/aeo-weekly.ts` — all active brands, all 4 engines, Mondays 13:00 UTC (≈8am ET, doesn't shift for DST), `maxDuration: 300`, concurrency-limited (3 brands at a time), gated on `CRON_SECRET`.
- `api/_lib/aeoAudit.ts` — shared runner + `generateBrief()`, used by both.

### 3.5 Frontend

`/tracker` route, linked in the main nav: brand cards (color-coded, linked to `cos_brands` scope/revenue-priority), live per-engine SoV bars from the latest audit's `engine_breakdown`, "Run Audit Now", expandable content-brief view (summary / gaps / recommended topics / recommended schema), full audit history table, per-engine OpenRouter model picker.

---

## 4. SOP — operating the Tracker

### 4.1 One-time setup (required before first use)
1. Apply `authority-engine/migrations/0001_aeo_cos_brands_link_and_briefs.sql` by hand in Supabase Studio against `supabase.insightprofit.live` (this instance has no SQL-exec RPC — same convention as every other migration in this org). This only *adds* columns/tables; it does not touch existing data.
2. Confirm Vercel env vars are present on the `authority-engine` project (production + preview): `SHS_URL`, `SHS_ANON`, `SHS_SERVICE`, `VITE_SHS_URL`, `VITE_SHS_ANON`, `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`, `CRON_SECRET`. Already wired as of this revision.
3. Merge `authority-engine` PR (AEO Tracker) once the migration above has run.

### 4.2 Running an audit
- Manual: open `authority.insightprofit.live/tracker`, pick models per engine slot if you want non-default ones, click "Run Audit Now" on a brand card. Takes up to ~2 minutes (4 engines × ~7 prompts, sequential per engine).
- Scheduled: the Monday cron runs all active brands automatically — no action needed.

### 4.3 Reading the output
- **SoV bars** on each brand card = mentions/total-queries per engine from the most recent audit.
- **"View brief"** = the agentic output: what the client is missing that competitors have, what to publish next, what schema to add.
- **Audit history table** = every run, including the recovered 2026-05/06 ones, with cost.

### 4.4 Adding a brand
Insert a row into `aeo_brands` with `cos_brand_id` set to the matching `cos_brands.id`, plus `aeo_competitors` rows. There are 19 brands in `cos_brands` total; only 5 have AEO tracking today (the original SOP's scope) — extending coverage to more is a future decision, not automatic.

### 4.5 Known limitations / next decisions (not blockers)
- Cost estimate is a flat $0.005/query heuristic (matches the historical rate already in the data), not per-model OpenRouter pricing — fine for budgeting, not exact.
- ChatGPT/Gemini/Claude engines have zero historical runs — first real-world test of those three happens on the next audit.
- `aeo.insightprofit.live` domain is unclaimed and untouched; decide separately whether to alias it to this app or retire it.

